# {{lb|en|by extension}} A speech or piece of writing which contains [[angry]] and [[extended#Adjective|extended]] [[criticism]]; a [[diatribe]], a [[harangue]]. {{defdate|from late 18th c.}}
#: {{synonyms|en|polemic|rant|tirade}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Paul Rees|title=‘We got off the coach and the National Front was there&nbsp;… People spat at us’|url=http://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/jul/25/west-brom-three-degrees-book-extract|newspaper={{w|The Guardian}}|date=25 July 2014|passage=One of the more regular correspondents to the club was an Everton fan, who'd send in an abusive '''screed''' each time Albion were due to play on Merseyside. He directed this at Atkinson, urging him not to select his "monkeys" for the game.}}
# ''Chiefly in the plural form'' '''{{l|en|screeds}}''': a [[large]] [[quantity]].
# {{senseid|en|tool}}{{lb|en|construction|masonry}} {{non-gloss definition|Senses relating to [[building#Noun|building]] construction and masonry.}}
## A [[tool#Noun|tool]], usually a long strip of [[wood]] or other [[material#Noun|material]], placed on a [[floor#Noun|floor]] to be [[cover#Verb|covered]] with [[concrete#Noun|concrete]], a [[wall#Noun|wall]] to be [[plaster#Verb|plastered]], etc., as a [[guide#Noun|guide]] for [[produce#Verb|producing]] a [[smooth#Adjective|smooth]], [[flat#Adjective|flat]] [[surface#Noun|surface]].
## A tool such as a long strip of wood or other material which is [[draw#Verb|drawn]] over a [[wet#Adjective|wet]] [[layer#Noun|layer]] of concrete, plaster, etc., to [[make#Verb|make]] it smooth and flat; also, a [[machine#Noun|machine]] that [[achieve]]s this [[effect#Noun|effect]]; a [[screeder]].
##: {{synonyms|en|strickle}}
## A smooth, flat layer of concrete, plaster, or similar material, especially if [[act#Verb|acting]] as a [[base#Noun|base]] for [[paving stone]]s, [[tile#Noun|tiles]], [[wooden]] [[plank#Noun|planks]], etc.

